Contributing to the wire-cell-phlex package.

Submitting contributions.

Contributions are accepted via Pull Requests (PRs) on GitHub.  By submitting a
PR, you agree that your contribution is licensed under the Apache License 2.0
and that you will be responsive to any requested changes to the PR prior to
merging.  Unwanted or neglected PRs may be closed without comment.

Use of large language models (LLMs).

We recognize LLMs as useful and acceptable tools for software development.

Any contribution to this package prepared with LLM assistance is considered to
be the work of the human submitter.  The human is expected to be responsible for
the contribution to the same extent as if they had prepared the contribution
without LLM assistance.

When LLMs are used to prepare a contribution, it is recomended but not required,
to include in the commit and/or the PR messages the names of LLM models used and
the manner in which they assisted.









